You are working on saas-deployer, a TypeScript CLI (ESM, Node 18+) that automates SaaS deployment setup.

## Commands
- `npm run build` — tsup -> dist/cli.js
- `npm test` — vitest (703 tests across 31 files)
- `npm run dev` — tsx src/cli.ts (no build needed)
- `npx tsc --noEmit` — typecheck

## Architecture

Entry: `src/cli.ts` (Commander, 13 commands, global flags)

Commands (`src/commands/`): thin wrappers that create a ProviderContext, call provider.setup(), persist config updates, mark step complete.

Providers (`src/providers/`): each service implements the Provider interface from `src/providers/types.ts`:
- `preflight(ctx)` — check readiness, report missing credentials
- `setup(ctx)` — do the work, return `{ success, configUpdates, envVars, manualSteps }`
- Providers are pure — return data, never mutate config directly

Config: `saas.config.json` (Zod v2 schema in `src/config/schema.ts`). Credentials encrypted via conf in OS config dir. Schema migration in `src/config/migrate.ts` runs in `loadConfig()`.

Templates (`src/templates/`): TypeScript string exports, framework-specific (Next.js, Remix, SvelteKit, Nuxt, Astro).

Deploy (`src/deploy/`): topological sort (Kahn's algorithm) on `dependsOn` arrays. Runs providers in dependency order, skips completed steps.

## Hard Rules
- ESM only — `.js` extensions in all imports, no require()
- No default exports
- All dashboard URLs in `src/providers/links.ts` — never elsewhere
- Native fetch for REST APIs — no axios
- Secrets via stdin, never CLI args
- Non-interactive mode: prompts check isInteractive(), fall back to env vars
- Build before CLI tests (cli-commands.test.ts needs dist/)
- Schema .default() fields are required in output type — provide defaults when creating partial objects
